cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on developing a positioning service for wireless networks, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses statistical models and estimation techniques to solve the localization problem, which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a distributed algorithm for cooperative localization, which can be considered as a control problem in a networked system. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper uses a hybrid approach combining two sensing modalities to reduce uncertainty, which can be seen as an application of AI techniques. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper deals with the problem of localizing multiple nodes in a network, which can be considered as a multiagent system.
